264
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,153
I'm sorry.

265
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:09,232
I don't enjoy sitting here
entertaining the pots and pans.

266
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,591
- Where are you?
- I'm right here, Mother.

267
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:16,840
Don't kiss me, dear.

268
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,911
I'm all full of egg white.

269
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,912
Oh, I'm exhausted.

270
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:23,514
When it got to be 6:00
and you still hadn't come...

271
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:27,229
...I thought, "Oh, my goodness,
she's correcting papers.

272
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:30,676
Shabab's will be closed and I bet
she forgot all about my chocolate bar. "

273
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:33,513
Oh. I did. I'm sorry.

274
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,193
I'm not criticizing, dear.

275
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,679
We all forget sometimes.

276
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,353
Anyhow, I got it myself.

277
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:40,829
I took a nice long walk in the heat.

278
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:46,115
Well, why don't you just lie down and
take a rest and I'll fix the sandwiches?

279
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,395
Oh, no, darling.

280
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:48,959
Really, I'm fine.

281
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,314
Truly, I am.

282
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:53,472
I just hope you're not coming down
with something.

283
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:54,640
Why? Should I be?

284
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:59,750
Well, dear, do that over here
where I can see you.

285
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,752
You have a fever?

286
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,273
- No.
- Here.

287
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,953
Give me your forehead.

288
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,916
Oh, just a little warm, that's all.

289
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:16,116
Mother, I'm always warm.

290
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:21,193
I heard the most awful thing
about the Stewart girl today.

291
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,715
Cassie Stewart has, shall we say...

292
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,074
...been away.

293
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:28,190
Been away with quotation marks?

294
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,635
Double quotation marks. Twins.

295
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,109
And no prospect of a husband in sight.

296
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,876
Can you imagine her poor mother?

297
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,110
She's a very nice woman. Really, she is.

298
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,840
Not too cultivated but very nice.

299
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,953
Oh, what a heartbreak for her.

300
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,120
Twins.

301
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:51,431
Yes, I suppose that must be
twice the heartbreak of one.

302
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,635
That's right, dear.

303
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,836
Just go ahead and make light of it.

304
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,991
Life is just a comedy to you.

305
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,669
She going to keep them?

306
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,751
Oh, that's what's so awful about it.
She is.

307
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,592
I found out all about it.

308
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:08,035
It was Mrs. Barnes that told me.

309
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:11,875
I ran into her this morning on the porch
at poor old Mr. Shoemaker's funeral.

310
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,959
And I said to her... I said... I said:

311
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:17,156
"Well, I thank my lucky stars...

312
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:22,269
...I never had one moment's worry
with either one of my daughters. "

313
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:26,279
Oh, Verla, you're not going to no-trump.

314
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:28,635
Oh, girls, isn't she the meanest thing?

315
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,950
Don't be a sore loser, May.

316
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:32,838
When you come to my house,
you can win.

317
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,069
Three hearts.

318
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,470
May I be a greedy piggy
and look at that candy box?

319
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:39,393
I think I'll just try
one of these peppermints.

320
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:42,757
Don't feel them, Florence.
You always feel everything.

321
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,399
I wish somebody would explain...

322
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:47,870
...why they keep putting
those green ones in with the limey taste.

323
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:51,669
If they're going to look like peppermints,
they should taste like peppermints.

324
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:52,955
Don't you agree?

325
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:55,395
Excuse me, but I have to go to bed now.

326
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,560
Oh.

327
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:58,631
Until later, dear.

328
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,153
Oh, my precious.

329
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:02,117
And I thank you so much.

330
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,793
Goodness, yes.

331
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:07,555
Well, those elegant sandwiches
were simply delicious.

332
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,039
So glad you enjoyed them.

333
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,633
Enjoyed them?

334
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:14,475
I'm not gonna be able
to haul myself out of this chair.

335
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:15,840
Good night.

336
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,911
Good night.
Good night.

337
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:20,551
I think Rachel is just marvelous.

338
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:24,039
I mean, the way she manages things.

339
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,953
And anybody who teaches
is an absolute saint.

340
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:29,429
Oh, she's always been wonderful.

341
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:10,480
Don't, Rachel.

342
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,073
Don't.

343
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:17,758
But it's just so I can sleep.

344
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,553
Don't.

345
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,995
Okay, everybody back. Come on.

346
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:47,391
Now, vacation hasn't started yet.
Don't push.

347
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:02,276
Goodbye, James.

348
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:56,434
"Some relations
with a double standard. "

349
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,952
What are you gonna have today, Rachel?

350
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:07,951
I'll have some, uh, cigarettes...

351
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:11,238
...and, uh, chocolate bars.

352
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:14,395
Oh, should I get some suntan lotion?

353
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,278
Take a small one, Rachel.

354
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:18,908
I'll give you a check
for the whole caboodle, all right?

355
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:21,116
Rachel Cameron.

356
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,553
Nick.

357
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,952
Nick Kazlik.

358
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:28,759
The one with the brother in the basket.

359
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,031
- You're staring.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

360
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,350
I don't think I would've recognized you.

361
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:37,318
I mean, we haven't seen each other
since high school.

362
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:39,835
Thought we'd have
your company at Leighton's.

363
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,792
Oh, were you the one? Oh.

364
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,632
I'll give you a chance to make it up.

365
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,030
- You wanna go to a movie tonight?
- What's playing?

366
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:48,352
What's the difference?

367
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:50,317
That'll be 4.02, Rachel.

368
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,311
Oh, thank you, Lee.

369
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,751
Well, actually, I couldn't go tonight...

370
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:58,959
...because I promised a friend
that I would go someplace with her.

371
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:03,432
Actually, I ought to be pointing my nose
in the direction of home right now.

372
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:06,033
Excuse me.

373
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:07,799
Thank you.

374
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:12,552
You still live in the same place?

375
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:16,870
Oh, yes, I keep house for my mother.

376
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,190
I have since my father died.

377
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:20,839
I didn't know he died.

378
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,399
There's no need for condolences.

379
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:24,516
It was 14 years ago.

380
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:27,148
That's a lot of housekeeping.

381
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:28,639
You didn't get to college?

382
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,553
Yes, I went to college.
But when he died, I had to come back.

383
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:35,679
You see, my mother sold the place
to Hector Jonas...

384
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:37,478
...for such a nominal sum...

385
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:40,950
...that, uh, he allowed us to live upstairs
in perpetuity.

386
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:45,315
Or at least until we were ready
to take our business downstairs to him.

387
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,512
I'm sorry, what did you ask me?

388
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,557
I'm a schoolteacher.

389
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:51,869
I didn't ask you.

390
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:53,075
But so am I.

391
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:54,389
Oh, in the city?

392
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:55,629
High school.

393
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:58,076
You teach high school in the city?

394
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:00,954
Why did you come back here?

395
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:02,997
T o see my folks.

396
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:05,720
They're beginning to slow down.

397
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,233
Another look.

398
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,992
That's all.

399
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:11,312
Well, I hope you have a nice visit.

400
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:14,159
Excuse me.

401
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,715
You wanna go to a movie
tomorrow night?

402
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:24,389
I don't like movies very much.

403
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:27,870
I mean, I see so many of them
on television.

404
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,116
How about your sister? Is she busy?

405
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:33,397
Oh, Stacey?
Stacey got married and moved away.

406
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:36,518
We don't see much of her
since she, uh, had her children.

407
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:38,395
And you got left behind?

408
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:42,675
Oh.

409
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,990
I forgot my galoshes.

410
00:28:48,120 --> 00:28:49,473
Hey.

411
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,914
Oh.

412
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,752
- Thank you.
Uh, no offense.

413
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:59,038
I was just looking for a little action.
I thought maybe you might be too.

414
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,191
Maybe I'll see you, Nick.

415
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:04,872
Excuse me.

416
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,440
Excuse me.

417
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:10,275
Oh, come on, Rachel,
we'll miss the beginning.

418
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:13,235
I'm a sleepwalker.

419
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:16,676
Have you by any chance
had yourself a little nipsy on the sly?

420
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:17,840
Sure.

421
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,877
First, an encounter at Shabab's.

422
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:23,077
And then home to the cooking sherry,
that's me.

423
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,077
Nothing's real.

424
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:29,355
Nothing is now.

425
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:32,512
If somebody pinched me,
I wouldn't even hurt.

426
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,950
I don't know, I've only got one life.

427
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:40,558
I say to myself, "Oh, maybe next time
this or that comes around, I'll grab it. "

428
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:43,678
But nothing ever comes around again,
ever, does it?

429
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:55,076
Don't chicken out.
It's nothing to be afraid of.

430
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,514
I know myself. I can't make...

431
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:59,956
You don't know anything about yourself.
Trust me.

432
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:04,989
Welcome, brother.

433
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,912
Lean on the Lord.

434
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:12,116
Calla, good to see you.

435
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:14,191
This is my friend, Rachel Cameron.

436
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:16,715
How are you?
Two seats right over there.

437
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,233
Love, baby.

438
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:56,311
- What?
- Love.

439
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,432
It's for you.

440
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:07,071
I'm sorry.

441
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:10,279
I don't know why I'm laughing.

442
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:12,431
Laughter's beautiful, baby. Be free.

443
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,029
Brothers and sisters!

444
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,200
Calla.

445
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:30,634
Shh. I'm right beside you.

446
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,836
Brothers and sisters...

447
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:36,470
...I'm just standing here...

448
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:38,596
...feeling so...

449
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,672
...blessed...

450
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:42,879
...and I have to tell you why.

451
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:45,754
I can't keep the joy inside me.

452
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:46,920
Listen to me.

453
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:49,958
Those of you who were here
one night last winter...

454
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:52,270
...remember that we had a visitor.

455
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,793
- Yes.
Yes.

456
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:57,430
A man who brought God
right into this room.

457
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,468
Brought the voice of the living God...

458
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:04,269
...right into this room
like a mighty rushing wind.

459
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,873
Praise God.
- Praise God.

460
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:08,110
- Praise God.
- Praise God.

461
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,711
He's here with us again.

462
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,632
Hallelujah.
Praise the Lord.

463
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:16,473
That man is sitting right there.

464
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:19,712
Right back in that dark kitchen.

465
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,599
Oh, my God. I'm so grateful.

466
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:24,352
- Calla, who is he?
Do you love him?

467
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,476
He's so beautiful,
I can't even describe him.

468
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,949
And he speaks in tongues.

469
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,473
Praise God.
- He does what?

470
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,551
- He's got the gift of tongues.
Praise God.

471
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:33,994
Praise God.

472
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,514
Close the doors, please.

473
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,309
Please, everyone, sit down.

474
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:21,310
I've been a lot of places
and something's happening.

475
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:27,236
But something is beginning to happen.

476
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:31,548
And not just with kids but all...

477
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,911
All kinds of people, all ages.

478
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,991
All over.

479
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:41,477
Maybe for the first time
since Jesus Christ.

480
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:44,110
You see, there's this...

481
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:46,191
...tremendous...

482
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:48,832
...yearning...

483
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:51,075
...to be...

484
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,913
...words.

485
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,397
- Words.
- Words.

486
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,074
Words and walls. Walls...

487
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:06,434
...between us. Chasms.

488
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:11,635
The animals are less alone
with roaring...

489
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:15,475
...than we are with all our words.

490
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,279
How we suffer.

491
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:25,158
How we...

492
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:29,395
...languish in the deep
and lifeless dungeons of ourselves.

493
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:32,350
We're cut off from each other.

494
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,431
We're cut off from God...

495
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:36,192
...and each other.

496
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:38,875
Oh, what can we do?

497
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:43,758
Can't we be what we are?

498
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,309
Isn't that our first and final obligation?

499
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,480
To be more...

500
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,599
...and more what we are?

501
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:54,229
More and more the image...

502
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:58,393
...God made us? His? Mine? Man's?

503
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:00,834
Look at your neighbor.

504
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:06,839
The human being in front or next to you
that you don't know. Look in his eye.

505
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,228
Now, who is he?

506
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:10,999
He's you.

507
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:14,038
And you're him
and you're both suffering...

508
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:18,637
...because you can't say what you want
to each other. What do you want to say?

509
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:23,388
What do you feel?

510
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:27,160
Love.

511
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,274
Say it again.

512
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:35,998
Love.

513
00:35:36,160 --> 00:35:37,513
Oh, say it, people.

514
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:39,193
Say it.

515
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,839
- Love.
Love.

516
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,672
Praise God.

517
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,671
With all your hearts, people, love.

518
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:45,840
Love.

519
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:50,399
Do you know what that is
to say that here?

520
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:54,236
In this life?

521
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:55,835
In this world?

522
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:59,038
It's happening.

523
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:01,634
Love that is given by God through us
to one another...

524
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:06,669
...the greatest gift of the spirit,
don't you feel it happening?

525
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,831
Don't you love the Lord
with all your hearts?

526
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:10,798
- Y es.
