01:17:22,120 --> 01:17:24,793
In what sense are you referring?

1048
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:27,711
Would you embalm them...

1049
01:17:27,880 --> 01:17:30,075
...together or separately?

1050
01:17:30,760 --> 01:17:32,432
You shock me, Rachel.

1051
01:17:32,600 --> 01:17:35,068
That's a terrible question.

1052
01:17:35,560 --> 01:17:38,597
I hope it was a purely scientific one.

1053
01:17:41,040 --> 01:17:43,873
I'd like to see where you do it.

1054
01:19:35,360 --> 01:19:37,316
In the name of God,
what are you doing?

1055
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:39,835
Get up. Come on. Get up.

1056
01:19:40,000 --> 01:19:42,070
Get up out of there. Come on. Get up.

1057
01:19:54,760 --> 01:19:56,159
May.

1058
01:19:56,640 --> 01:19:58,073
May.

1059
01:19:58,280 --> 01:19:59,872
May!

1060
01:20:00,040 --> 01:20:02,156
Come take her from me.
She's been in the room.

1061
01:20:02,320 --> 01:20:05,437
Don't stand there, woman.
She has to be scrubbed right away.

1062
01:20:12,280 --> 01:20:13,918
Hector...

1063
01:20:16,400 --> 01:20:19,039
...would you mind putting
your arm around me?

1064
01:20:19,200 --> 01:20:21,270
Not at all.

1065
01:20:24,960 --> 01:20:26,632
Oh, God.

1066
01:20:26,800 --> 01:20:29,189
I wish I wasn't losing my hair.

1067
01:20:29,360 --> 01:20:31,351
Hector, things like that don't matter.

1068
01:20:31,520 --> 01:20:33,272
- Oh, they do, they do...
- No, they don't.

1069
01:20:33,440 --> 01:20:35,874
...if you're getting bald.

1070
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:37,758
They do.

1071
01:20:38,120 --> 01:20:40,429
Hector, help me.

1072
01:20:40,720 --> 01:20:41,755
How?

1073
01:20:41,920 --> 01:20:44,992
Sometimes I can't even tie my shoelace.

1074
01:20:45,160 --> 01:20:49,039
I think I've done something
that's going to finish my mother.

1075
01:20:49,920 --> 01:20:52,434
You oughtn't to tell me things like that.

1076
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:55,071
I don't know. I don't know anything.

1077
01:20:56,360 --> 01:20:58,749
If I gave you the wrong advice,
can you imagine?

1078
01:20:59,600 --> 01:21:00,749
But you know.

1079
01:21:03,720 --> 01:21:06,712
Oh, the only thing I'm good for...

1080
01:21:07,960 --> 01:21:10,918
...is to tell you where to go to have it...

1081
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:13,479
...you know...

1082
01:21:13,880 --> 01:21:15,393
Killed?

1083
01:21:50,760 --> 01:21:52,557
Who is it?

1084
01:21:52,760 --> 01:21:54,352
It's me, Rachel.

1085
01:21:54,520 --> 01:21:55,635
Rachel?

1086
01:21:58,600 --> 01:22:00,318
Have you any idea what time it is?

1087
01:22:01,680 --> 01:22:03,477
Well, it's 3:00.

1088
01:22:04,480 --> 01:22:06,391
I think that's a helluva nerve.

1089
01:22:08,720 --> 01:22:14,636
Well, I'm a very drunk,
very pregnant lady and I need a friend.

1090
01:22:26,120 --> 01:22:29,271
I'm out of saccharine,
can you stand sugar?

1091
01:22:29,440 --> 01:22:31,192
I just take milk.

1092
01:22:34,280 --> 01:22:36,635
You know, if I think about...

1093
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:38,951
...having it...

1094
01:22:39,720 --> 01:22:42,553
...without considering anybody else...

1095
01:22:42,960 --> 01:22:44,996
...it just seems like...

1096
01:22:46,200 --> 01:22:48,475
What? Finish it.

1097
01:22:50,480 --> 01:22:53,916
More than anything I could hope for
in my whole life.

1098
01:22:56,200 --> 01:22:57,269
Without Nick?

1099
01:22:58,120 --> 01:23:00,270
Oh, he wasn't real.

1100
01:23:00,880 --> 01:23:02,757
I made him up.

1101
01:23:04,040 --> 01:23:06,554
But it's living there, all by itself.

1102
01:23:07,880 --> 01:23:09,074
Inside of me.

1103
01:23:09,240 --> 01:23:11,708
I never thought anything...

1104
01:23:12,360 --> 01:23:15,079
...alive could ever grow in me.

1105
01:23:21,600 --> 01:23:23,477
You think I could?

1106
01:23:29,640 --> 01:23:31,517
You think I'd dare?

1107
01:23:33,480 --> 01:23:35,198
If you did...

1108
01:23:35,720 --> 01:23:37,551
...this could be
the first decision you made...

1109
01:23:37,720 --> 01:23:40,359
...that showed any respect for yourself.

1110
01:24:06,120 --> 01:24:08,031
Mrs. James?

1111
01:24:09,080 --> 01:24:11,514
You look like a healthy woman,
blood pressure's normal.

1112
01:24:11,680 --> 01:24:12,874
Your heart's still beating.

1113
01:24:13,040 --> 01:24:15,315
That's... That's nice.

1114
01:24:21,960 --> 01:24:25,316
Whoops.
We don't want that cotton anymore.

1115
01:24:28,520 --> 01:24:29,794
Okay?

1116
01:24:32,960 --> 01:24:34,234
Chicago? I know Chicago.

1117
01:24:34,400 --> 01:24:37,153
Where's Cannon Street?

1118
01:24:38,040 --> 01:24:39,393
It's, uh...

1119
01:24:39,720 --> 01:24:42,314
Oh, it's just out by the lake.

1120
01:24:42,480 --> 01:24:45,631
One of those ritzy
North Side neighborhoods, huh?

1121
01:24:45,800 --> 01:24:47,472
I guess so.

1122
01:24:49,640 --> 01:24:51,392
Any complications so far?

1123
01:24:51,560 --> 01:24:53,118
- No, should there be?
No.

1124
01:24:53,280 --> 01:24:56,033
- Thirty-five is just a little late to start.
- Oh.

1125
01:24:56,640 --> 01:24:57,834
Now, let's lie down.

1126
01:24:58,000 --> 01:24:59,877
What...?
- It's all right, just lie down.

1127
01:25:00,040 --> 01:25:01,040
That's it.

1128
01:25:01,200 --> 01:25:03,077
Try to think of his college education.

1129
01:25:03,240 --> 01:25:05,151
Now, try to relax.

1130
01:25:07,360 --> 01:25:08,839
I am. I'm sorry.

1131
01:25:12,200 --> 01:25:15,192
All right, now try to relax now,
Mrs. James.

1132
01:26:00,680 --> 01:26:02,830
Okay, you can sit up now.

1133
01:26:03,720 --> 01:26:05,153
You all right?

1134
01:26:06,360 --> 01:26:08,828
I'm afraid Junior's not planning
to visit you just yet...

1135
01:26:09,000 --> 01:26:10,797
...but I'm glad you came in
when you did.

1136
01:26:10,960 --> 01:26:11,995
What do you mean?

1137
01:26:12,160 --> 01:26:13,718
It's not what we thought it was.

1138
01:26:13,880 --> 01:26:15,757
There's something there,
it's causing the symptoms...

1139
01:26:15,920 --> 01:26:17,512
...and it ought to come out.

1140
01:26:18,280 --> 01:26:19,349
What ought to come out?

1141
01:26:19,520 --> 01:26:21,556
It's just a small cyst.

1142
01:26:21,720 --> 01:26:23,870
It's nothing to be concerned about.

1143
01:26:26,440 --> 01:26:28,032
Is that all?

1144
01:26:28,200 --> 01:26:30,270
It couldn't be anything else.

1145
01:26:33,280 --> 01:26:36,352
I'm sorry, Mrs. James. Would you like
to be left alone for a minute?

1146
01:26:56,080 --> 01:26:57,752
Oh, God.

1147
01:27:25,680 --> 01:27:27,750
Rachel Cameron says she'll die

1148
01:27:27,920 --> 01:27:29,114
For the want of the Golden City

1149
01:27:29,280 --> 01:27:30,554
Lazy Mary, will you get up?

1150
01:27:30,720 --> 01:27:31,720
Will you get up?

1151
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:33,472
Rachel, is that you out there?

1152
01:27:33,640 --> 01:27:35,596
Come on, wide-awake now.

1153
01:27:35,760 --> 01:27:36,988
Good morning, Rachel dear.

1154
01:27:37,160 --> 01:27:40,038
You keep pining for a life of your own...

1155
01:27:40,200 --> 01:27:43,988
...but somehow, with you and her,
it always turns out to be bridge night.

1156
01:27:44,160 --> 01:27:46,833
Where are you?
I'm counting. One's used up now.

1157
01:27:47,000 --> 01:27:48,831
That's a girl. Come on, now.

1158
01:27:49,000 --> 01:27:51,150
You know what happens
when I get to three.

1159
01:27:51,520 --> 01:27:52,953
Two.

1160
01:27:53,360 --> 01:27:55,157
Two and a half.

1161
01:27:55,320 --> 01:27:57,151
Two and three-quarters.

1162
01:28:00,560 --> 01:28:02,232
The operation is over.

1163
01:28:02,400 --> 01:28:04,436
You' re out of danger.

1164
01:28:05,320 --> 01:28:09,472
How can I be out of danger
if I'm not dead?

1165
01:28:11,560 --> 01:28:13,630
You'll be all right.

1166
01:28:15,320 --> 01:28:17,436
Well, just look at you.

1167
01:28:17,600 --> 01:28:20,398
All fed and rested.

1168
01:28:21,280 --> 01:28:24,238
Would I ever love
to change places with you?

1169
01:28:26,440 --> 01:28:28,032
Oh, before I forget.

1170
01:28:28,200 --> 01:28:31,237
I brought the stationery like I promised.

1171
01:28:31,480 --> 01:28:33,072
And I forgot something. What else?

1172
01:28:33,240 --> 01:28:36,516
Mother, I don't like to plunge into this
like this...

1173
01:28:36,680 --> 01:28:40,070
...but there's just...
Is no graceful way of doing it.

1174
01:28:40,240 --> 01:28:43,755
Calla helped me to apply
for a teaching job in Oregon...

1175
01:28:43,920 --> 01:28:47,674
...and I was accepted.
And I'm moving there next month.

1176
01:28:52,080 --> 01:28:53,354
Oh...

1177
01:28:53,600 --> 01:28:56,239
Drat. I forgot the stamps.

1178
01:28:57,320 --> 01:29:00,596
- I forgot the stamps.
- Would you stop fidgeting in your bag...

1179
01:29:00,760 --> 01:29:03,399
...and look at me for once, please?

1180
01:29:04,440 --> 01:29:06,237
Did you hear what I had to say?

1181
01:29:07,280 --> 01:29:08,918
It's too silly to hear.

1182
01:29:10,040 --> 01:29:11,871
It's not silly.

1183
01:29:12,400 --> 01:29:16,359
- If you want a little change, I...
- I don't want a little change.

1184
01:29:16,520 --> 01:29:19,876
There's no reason to be moving.

1185
01:29:20,360 --> 01:29:21,759
Move. Why?

1186
01:29:23,880 --> 01:29:25,836
Because it's time.

1187
01:29:28,520 --> 01:29:31,114
Now, I have already gotten my ticket...

1188
01:29:31,280 --> 01:29:35,558
...and if you want to go with me,
I'll give you the money for yours.

1189
01:29:40,560 --> 01:29:43,711
We'll discuss that when you get home,
you know.

1190
01:29:44,840 --> 01:29:47,229
You'll get to see your grandchildren.

1191
01:29:51,720 --> 01:29:53,950
I don't want to move, Rachel.

1192
01:29:54,600 --> 01:29:56,033
Then don't.

1193
01:30:00,360 --> 01:30:04,353
- You know I can't be left alone, that's...
- Then come with me.

1194
01:30:04,840 --> 01:30:07,035
Doctor doesn't want me to exert myself.

1195
01:30:07,200 --> 01:30:09,794
All you'd have to do is get on a bus.

1196
01:30:18,320 --> 01:30:20,515
I don't want to, Rachel.

1197
01:30:20,680 --> 01:30:23,956
Please! Please. Please.

1198
01:30:24,120 --> 01:30:27,556
You don't want to what? You don't
want to go or you don't want to stay?

1199
01:30:29,080 --> 01:30:31,719
I don't want to.

1200
01:30:33,680 --> 01:30:37,434
You're the cruelest thing that ever lived.

1201
01:30:39,800 --> 01:30:42,951
Don't you care what happens to me?

1202
01:30:43,760 --> 01:30:46,593
After all those sleepy-bye pills...

1203
01:30:46,920 --> 01:30:49,639
...and chocolate bars
and sandwiches and walks...

1204
01:30:49,800 --> 01:30:51,836
...can you ask me that?

1205
01:30:54,120 --> 01:30:55,917
Yes, I care.

1206
01:30:57,120 --> 01:30:58,712
But I can't keep you alive.

1207
01:30:58,880 --> 01:31:00,757
That's not up to me.

1208
01:31:01,320 --> 01:31:03,038
Never was.

1209
01:31:08,480 --> 01:31:10,630
Would I have to sell my furniture?

1210
01:31:12,760 --> 01:31:15,593
Couldn't I even take my room?

1211
01:31:20,280 --> 01:31:22,748
Y es, you can take your room.

1212
01:31:24,040 --> 01:31:26,873
You can take anything you like.

1213
01:31:27,800 --> 01:31:29,472
Mother. Mama.

1214
01:31:29,640 --> 01:31:30,755
Mommy.

1215
01:31:31,240 --> 01:31:32,992
All the way back.

1216
01:31:33,160 --> 01:31:38,280
Such a long, sad, lonely, awful time.

1217
01:32:02,440 --> 01:32:04,271
The moment comes.

1218
01:32:04,720 --> 01:32:08,395
I'm always pushing things
out of their cages.

1219
01:32:10,920 --> 01:32:12,478
Calla.

1220
01:32:12,920 --> 01:32:15,673
Sometimes I wish
I could've been different for you.

1221
01:32:16,680 --> 01:32:19,274
Y eah, well, don't go making
a fool of yourself.

1222
01:32:19,440 --> 01:32:21,192
You know how you feel about fools.

1223
01:32:24,760 --> 01:32:27,035
Maybe I'm proud to be one.

1224
01:32:45,840 --> 01:32:47,273
Calla.

1225
01:32:49,600 --> 01:32:51,158
Take care.

1226
01:32:51,920 --> 01:32:53,353
I hope you find what you want.

1227
01:32:54,920 --> 01:32:57,388
Not to worry. I'll survive.

1228
01:33:17,360 --> 01:33:19,920
The wind blows low, the wind blows high

1229
01:33:20,080 --> 01:33:21,911
The snow comes falling from the sky

1230
01:33:22,080 --> 01:33:23,832
Rachel Cameron says she'll die

1231
01:33:24,000 --> 01:33:26,230
For the want of the Golden City

1232
01:33:26,400 --> 01:33:28,516
She is handsome, she is pretty

1233
01:33:28,680 --> 01:33:30,989
She's the queen of the Golden City

1234
01:33:31,160 --> 01:33:32,991
She is pretty, one, two, three

1235
01:33:33,160 --> 01:33:35,549
In the Golden City

1236
01:33:35,720 --> 01:33:37,790
The wind said, " When?"
The wind said, "Soon "

1237
01:33:37,960 --> 01:33:40,394
The dream comes flying from the moon

1238
01:33:40,560 --> 01:33:42,232
Rachel Cameron sings the tune

1239
01:33:42,400 --> 01:33:45,073
At the gates of the Golden City

1240
01:33:45,240 --> 01:33:47,390
They are happy, they are pretty

1241
01:33:47,560 --> 01:33:50,358
All who dwell in the Golden City
They are happy...

1242
01:33:50,520 --> 01:33:53,273
Where I'm going anything may happen.

1243
01:33:53,760 --> 01:33:55,716
Nothing may happen.

1244
01:34:00,880 --> 01:34:03,155
Maybe I'll find a friend.

1245
01:34:06,280 --> 01:34:08,350
Maybe I'll even marry
a middle-aged widower...

1246
01:34:08,520 --> 01:34:10,829
...and have children in my time.

1247
01:34:13,800 --> 01:34:16,519
Most of the chances are against it...

1248
01:34:16,680 --> 01:34:19,069
...but not, I think, quite all.

1249
01:34:23,200 --> 01:34:26,431
It may be that my children
will always be temporary...

1250
01:34:26,600 --> 01:34:28,511
...never to be held.

1251
01:34:30,720 --> 01:34:32,676
But so are everyone's.

1252
01:34:40,720 --> 01:34:42,915
I will be afraid.

1253
01:34:43,160 --> 01:34:44,832
Always.

1254
01:34:47,280 --> 01:34:50,192
I may be lonely always.

1255
01:34:52,960 --> 01:34:54,757
What will happen?

1256
01:34:59,240 --> 01:35:01,310
What will happen?

